  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 180°C/ 160°C (fan)/ gas 4, take your<strong> chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Bash your <strong>cucumber</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> and chop it into large, bite-sized pieces (Tip: Bash the cucumber in its bag to avoid mess!), then deseed your <strong>sweet pointed pepper[s] </strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop roughly</p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Chop half your cucumber and sweet pointed pepper into batons</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1688730257092-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1688730257092-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1688730257092-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1688730257092-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1688730257092-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Soak your <strong>skewers </strong>in <strong>cold water </strong>(this prevents them from burning whilst cooking)</p><p>Chop your <strong>chicken breast portion[s]</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add your<strong> soy sauce</strong> to a large bowl with your <strong>honey</strong>, <strong>half </strong>your <strong>mayo</strong> and <strong>half </strong>your <strong>sesame seeds </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) – this is your <strong>sesame marinade</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Leave out the sesame seeds or just add a little!</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1688730261064-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1688730261064-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1688730261064-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1688730261064-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1688730261064-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer <strong>half </strong>your <strong>marinade</strong> to a separate small bowl and set aside</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped chicken</strong> to the large bowl of <strong>sesame marinade</strong> and give everything a good mix up until fully coated</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1717760724532-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1717760724532-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1717760724532-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1717760724532-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1717760724532-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Thread the <strong>marinated chicken </strong>onto the <strong>soaked skewers</strong> – these are your <strong>chicken skewers</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chicken skewers</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) and pull up the edges of the foil to form an open parcel (this will collect any juices!)</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 18-20 minutes, turning once halfway, until golden and cooked through (no pink meat!) – these are your <strong>honey sesame chicken skewers</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1688730275371-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1688730275371-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1688730275371-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1688730275371-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1688730275371-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> to a pot with 225ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/23-05-24_08h55m55s-APIC-1717760892161-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/23-05-24_08h55m55s-APIC-1717760892161-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/23-05-24_08h55m55s-APIC-1717760892161-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/23-05-24_08h55m55s-APIC-1717760892161-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/23-05-24_08h55m55s-APIC-1717760892161-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While your rice and chicken skewers are cooking, add your <strong>rice vinegar </strong>to a bowl with your <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong>, <strong>remaining sesame seeds</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!),<strong> </strong>and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> – this is your <strong>spicy dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/23-05-24_09h00m02s-APIC-1717760927682-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/23-05-24_09h00m02s-APIC-1717760927682-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/23-05-24_09h00m02s-APIC-1717760927682-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/23-05-24_09h00m02s-APIC-1717760927682-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/23-05-24_09h00m02s-APIC-1717760927682-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>smashed cucumber </strong>and <strong>chopped pepper</strong> to the spicy dressing and mix it all together</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>– this is your <strong>spicy smashed cucumber salad</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Leave the pepper and cucumber batons plain!</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1717760987384-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1717760987384-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1717760987384-x700.jpg",
